# My everyday loaf based on morph

starter:
  rye
  water
  hydration = 100%

leaven ^ 6g:
  starter
  ww = 4 * starter
  water
  hydration = 100%

grain:
  prairie_gold
  hard_red = prairie_gold
  spelt = 5%
  barley = 5%
  buckwheat = 5%

dry:
  grain
  vwg = 3%
  potato_flakes = 3%
  flaxseed_meal = 5%
  yeast = 0.5%
  salt = 1.8%

wet:
  water
  ascorbic_acid_1p = 50ppm * 100 * grain.total
  leaven = 30%
  olive_oil = 5%
  malt_syrup = 5%
  yogurt = 5%

dough:
  wet
  dry
  walnuts = 15%
  hydration = 70%
  # 200g/L of flour
  # total_flour = 660g # 13 inch
  total_flour = 460g # 9 inch

/*
April 8, 2026

Changes
• back to ww in leaven
• add walnuts, blanched

Zoji pan weighs 773g. KA pan weighs 725g.

Starter is 5 days old.

Mixed the leaven with 60F water about 17:10 left at 60F overnight.
Initial leaven temperature is 67F. RT is 75F.

Leaven pH = 4.43 at 8:05. More than doubled. At 275mL.

I started about 8:02

Dry is 76F. Wet is 52F. Mix is 64F.

Used the KA for mixing. Mixed about 8:35. Stopped after 3 minutes.
DT after mixing is 64F. RT is 68F. 

30 minute rest in fridge. After rest the dough is 61F outside

Restarted the KA for kneading. Removed the dough after 8 minutes of
kneading. Finished at 9:20.

DT at end of kneading is 68F. Into the cambro for 30 minutes in the
fridge. S&F, back to the fridge for 30 more.

Shaped at 10:30 and into the pan. Proof at 76F.

120mL of water lasted for less than 15 (maybe 12?) minutes into the bake.

Baked at 14:15 for 40 minutes at 350F. It was about 1/2 inch above
the top of the pan.

Close to perfect appearance. Good flavor.

*/


